--- title: "Matching and Subclassification" author: "Lucas Rousselange" execute: warning: false format: html: code-fold: true number-sections: false --- ::: {.cell hash='07_matching_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-1_e0d4ef3e422fbda0cc280eedce3ee09f'} ```{.r .cell-code} #Load data set and libraries library(ggplot2) library(tidyverse) library(RColorBrewer) library(dagitty) library(ggdag) library(jtools) library(kableExtra) library(MatchIt) membership <- readRDS("../../../Causal_Data_Science_Data/membership.rds") ``` ::: # Task 1 ## Exploring the relationships Plotting a heat map for the available factors, there seems to be a high correlation between age, average purchase and pre membership average purchase.The pre membership average purchase, age and membership card also seem correlated. The sex seems to not have a big influence on either variable. ::: {.cell hash='07_matching_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-2_688189f4270608b2f5bb5ec0b4dda764'} ```{.r .cell-code} mem_cor <- as.data.frame(cor(membership)) mem_heat <- mem_cor %>% rownames_to_column() %>% gather(colname, value, -rowname) ggplot(mem_heat, aes(x=colname,y=rowname, fill=value)) + geom_tile(color='black')+ scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = 'blue4')+ geom_text(aes(label = round(value,2)), color = "black", size = 4) + labs(x='', y='', title = 'Heatmap correlation between variables') ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](07_matching_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: ## DAG ::: {.cell hash='07_matching_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-3_c5119bdf885c005ad5801ed49e8ab443'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Confounder confounding <- dagify( X ~ Z1, Y ~ Z1, Y ~ X, X ~ Z2, Y ~ Z2, Z2 ~ Z1, coords = list(x = c(Y = 3, Z1 = 1, X = 1, Z2=3), y = c(Y = 0, Z1 = 1, X = 0, Z2 =1)), labels = list(Z2 = "pre_avg_purch", Y = "avg_purch", Z1 = "age", X= 'card') ) p <- ggdag(confounding) + geom_dag_point(color = "#15c1d4") + geom_dag_text(color = "white") + geom_dag_edges(edge_color = "black") + geom_dag_label_repel(aes(label = label))+ theme_dag_blank() p ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](07_matching_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: # Task 2 Naive model: ::: {.cell hash='07_matching_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-4_863dedd5cc33dfed26fd27dccc5141a8'} ```{.r .cell-code} lm_naive <- lm(avg_purch ~ card, data = membership) summ(lm_naive) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}

Pair Dist. #> age 0.0067 0.1224 #> pre_avg_purch 0.0133 0.1557 #> #> Sample Sizes: #> Control Treated #> All 5768. 4232. #> Matched (ESS) 5527.11 3928.04 #> Matched 5752. 4199. #> Unmatched 16. 33. #> Discarded 0. 0. ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} df_cem <- match.data(cem) lm_cem <- lm(avg_purch ~ card, data = df_cem, weights = weights) summ(lm_cem) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}

Error z value Pr(>|z|) #> (Intercept) -1.4121735 0.0723729 -19.512 <2e-16 *** #> age 0.0011734 0.0017758 0.661 0.509 #> pre_avg_purch 0.0148181 0.0009263 15.996 <2e-16 *** #> --- #> Signif. codes: 0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1 #> #> (Dispersion parameter for binomial family taken to be 1) #> #> Null deviance: 13626 on 9999 degrees of freedom #> Residual deviance: 13250 on 9997 degrees of freedom #> AIC: 13256 #> #> Number of Fisher Scoring iterations: 4 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # Add propensities to table membership_aug <- membership %>% mutate(propensity = predict(model_prop, type = "response")) # Extend data by IPW scores membership_ipw <- membership_aug %>% mutate( ipw = (card/propensity) + ((1-card) / (1-propensity))) # Run with high weights excluded lm_ipw <- lm(avg_purch ~ card, data = membership_ipw %>% filter(propensity %>% between(0.15, 0.85)), weights = ipw) summ(lm_ipw) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
